16:17:47 <HarshPandit> Subtopic: AI Documentation
20:10:04 <ghurlbot> https://github.com/w3c/dpv/issues/94 -> Issue 94 Represent Datasheets and Model Cards with DPV (by coolharsh55)
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> FabianLinde: Analysing the AI Act for documentation requirements (currently at around 280) and then looking at approaches like Data Sheets, Model Cards, ISO 42001, to see if you already have these documentation then how much of the AI Act you already have the information for. Also looking at DPV and MLDCAT-AP and what are gaps, and then how to fill in the gaps through proposed concepts.
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> BeatrizEsteves: does this include looking at policies on how AI should be used?
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> FabianLinde: Yes, you have to document acceptable use policies, which is an item you have to tick the box for to complete the documentation
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> DelaramGolpayegani: I think Dave also have a Masters student who is looking at this with the plan to propose concepts into DPV
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> BeatrizEsteves: BTW being discussed right now on ODRL CG: https://github.com/w3c/odrl/issues/147
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> HarshPandit: Please share our work on this e.g. https://dev.dpvcg.org/2.4-dev/ai/#ModelTraining where we already put AI training as a processing operation
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> DelaramGolpayegani: Also the work done on AIUP (co-authored with Beatriz) https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-3759/paper17.pdf to share with them
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> DelaramGolpayegani: Looking at the AI Act, the scope is relevant, for AIUP we only looked at Provider and Deployer. E.g. for procurement. 
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> HarshPandit: Agree, for ODRL suggest only keeping Training as Action and then having a separate profile that goes into depth for specific use-cases / perspectives
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> DelaramGolpayegani: Can the action be defined in DPV?
16:17:47 <HarshPandit> BeatrizEsteves: Yes, we can tell them use the DPV profile (as and when created), but there will be people who want to use only/pure ODRL. So when they have the action there that allows them using the ODRL purpose and the DPV taxonomy. So ODRL want this action in the (main) ODRL vocab.
